{title: I Wasted A Nickel Last Night}
{artist: Hawkshaw Hawkins}
{composer: written by Shorty Long and Bob Newman}

[G]I put a nickel in the telephone
[C]To find out dear if you'd be home
[D7]I wasted a nickel last [G]night
I guess I've wished a million times
[C]It hadn't been a party line
[D7]I wasted a nickel last [G]night
I [C]heard you tell a friend of mine
[G]That I was not the one
[A7]Why did you play me for a fool
[D7]So you could have your fun
[G]If I had known it from the start
[C]It might have saved a broken heart
[D7]The nickel I wasted last [G]night
I lost a nickel but I lost much more
[C]It seems I hear it o'er and o'er
[D7]I wasted a nickel last [G]night
My castles have all fallen down
[C]I saw them tumble to the ground
[D7]A nickel changed it all last [G]night
But [C]someday when your world gets lonely
[G]And your friends are few
[A7]The door of love is open dear
[D7]I'm waiting here for you
[G]A nickel has it's story told
[C]Of love not worth its weight in gold
[D7]I wasted a nickel last [G]night